{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d78f2614-e24d-422b-9595-5c4fb14b4d04","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's a summary:\n\n## 1. Lost test history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed how **test IDs** are generated — they now use fully qualified names (`Namespace.Class.Method`) instead of just the method name. Azure DevOps matches history by test ID, so every test appears \"new.\"\n\n**No code fix needed** — history will rebuild over subsequent runs.\n\n## 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is a **class-level** context with no associated test. Accessing `TestName` throws `InvalidOperationException` because `ClassInitialize` runs once before any test method.\n\nYour fix — remove the `TestName` usage from `ClassInit`:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // context.TestName is not available here in MSTest v4.\n    // Use TestContext only for class-level setup (e.g., logging, shared resources).\n}\n```\n\nIf you need per-test names at setup time, move that logic to `[TestInitialize]` where the instance-level `TestContext` is fully populated.\n\n## 3. Other v4 pitfalls to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Parallel execution** | Now enabled by default at the **method** level. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or `[assembly: DoNotParallelize]` if your tests aren't thread-safe. |\n| **Assert.ThrowsException** | Now validates the **exact** exception type (no subclass matching). Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` / `Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync` for the old exact behavior, or update expectations. |\n| **Timeout** | `[Timeout]` now uses `CancellationToken` via `TestContext.CancellationTokenSource`; cooperative cancellation is preferred over thread-abort. |\n| **`[ExpectedException]`** | Deprecated in favor of `Assert.ThrowsException`. Still works but may emit warnings. |\n| **Lifecycle ordering** | `[AssemblyCleanup]` / `[ClassCleanup]` timing is stricter — cleanup methods now run deterministically after all tests in scope complete. |\n\nThe parallel-by-default change is the most likely to cause surprise failures in existing suites. I'd start there if you see intermittent test failures after the upgrade.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1d8402d5-5335-4981-bc09-ff93cb713bc3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about MSTest v4 migration issues. Let me research the known breaking changes in MSTest v4 to give them accurate information. I know several key changes:\n\n1. **Fully qualified test IDs** — MSTest v4 changed test ID generation to use fully qualified names, which causes Azure DevOps (and other CI systems) to lose test history because the IDs no longer match.\n\n2. **TestContext in ClassInitialize** — In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` methods is no longer associated with a specific test, so `TestContext.TestName` throws (or returns null). This is because `ClassInitialize` runs once for the class, not per-test.\n   \n3. **Additional breaking changes** — There are also shifts in how `DeploymentItem` works, potential changes to parallel execution defaults, modifications to the `DataRow` attribute, and adjustments to the assembly and class initialization/cleanup lifecycle. Let me verify the specifics of these changes to give accurate guidance.\n\nLooking at what I know about MSTest v4, the `TestContext` behavior in `[ClassInitialize]` is particularly important — it's now a class-level context without test-specific properties like `TestName`, so accessing those throws an error. Beyond that, I should cover floating point assertion comparisons, the status of `ExpectedException`, timeout handling, how `TestCleanup` behaves with skipped tests, and parallelization shifts. I want to give them practical migration advice tailored to their situation.","outputTokens":1128,"requestId":"3413:3F01EB:E62FB:1196AC:69F415B6"},"id":"9515cc59-9654-4ba2-ba70-9141b0eed8eb","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:54:06.762Z","parentId":"b6af40fa-7341-4a3b-a09b-327c898e68ab"}
